parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of ignition coils can cause the engine to misfire, leading to poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially causing the engine to stall, which can lead to accidents.

Leaks in the valve cover gasket can cause oil to leak into the spark plug wells, leading to engine misfires, poor engine performance, and potentially causing the engine to stall, which can lead to accidents.
Failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, poor engine performance, and potentially causing the engine to stall, which can lead to accidents.
Failure of the electrical system can cause various electrical components to malfunction, leading to poor vehicle performance, decreased safety, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: vehicle stalling while at a stop light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of power steering and power brakes, leading to decreased vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the wheel to become loose, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud squeaking or clunking sounds from the front of the vehicle
difficulty maintaining control of the vehicle
